He's a lazy, crazy, sorry,
no-good bag of bones.

74
00:04:52,300 --> 00:04:54,400
So what you laughing at?

75
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,600
All pushcarts
to the start position!

76
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:01,300
- Ready, little man?
- Ready, big man.

77
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:03,500
Kiss the lucky egg.

78
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,700
Let's go!

79
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:11,600
- On your marks...
- Feel the rhythm! Feel the rhyme!

80
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:14,300
Get on up!
It's pushcart time!

81
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:16,600
and go !

82
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:24,700
Here we go, Winston!
The Rockett has been launched!

83
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:27,200
Hey, fruitcake!
Where'd you get that cart?

84
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:30,100
Clear out!
Come on, move out! Look out!

85
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:34,500
Sanka Coffie,
pushcart champion!

86
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:37,600
- Pushcart champion!
- Get away! Get away!

87
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,900
Hey, grandma, out of my way!

88
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:45,300
Hey, Sunday driver, make room
for the Rasta Rockett! Make room!

89
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:48,700
- Sanka, four more carts left!
- Pee Wee, move! Move out!

90
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:52,800
I love Jamaica,
and Jamaica loves me!

91
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:55,900
Champion! Champion!
You can't mess with the best!

92
00:05:56,100 --> 00:06:00,400
- Move over! Move over!
- Get away! Get off me!

93
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:02,200
- Go, Sanka!
- Get him! Get him!

94
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:05,500
One more cart left!
Go! Go! Go! Go!

95
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:07,900
Yes! We win!

96
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:14,200
Jump, Winston, jump!

97
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,200
Sanka!

98
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,200
Move it, man!
Move, move, move!

99
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:36,000
Sanka, you dead?

100
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:38,000
Yeah, man.

101
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:45,600
And where do you think
you're going?

102
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,900
You caught me.

103
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:51,400
- You have papers to grade.
- I'm just getting in one last run.

104
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:57,100
I can't believe the tryouts
are finally here.

105
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:01,400
- You nervous?
- I'm not nervous.

106
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:05,800
I'm ready. I've been ready
for this day my whole life.

107
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:10,000
I don't care how fast they run,
I'm going to run faster.

108
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:14,500
I don't care how much
they want it, I want it more.

109
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:17,700
I'm going to the Olympics, baby.

110
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:22,400
I feel it.
I'm going to win the gold.

111
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:26,300
Derice, are you nervous?

112
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,400
I'm terrified.

113
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:37,500
It's my turn, Joy!
It's my turn!

114
00:07:39,300 --> 00:07:42,500
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the final event...

115
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,500
of today's Olympic tryouts.

116
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:50,300
We have now come to the
main event of our games...

117
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:54,200
the running
of the 100-metre finals.

118
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:56,700
We've had a most
successful afternoon...

119
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,600
and I'd like to congratulate
all the athletes...

120
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,800
who have participated
in today's events.

121
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:06,500
- You sure no one can beat him?
- Oh, sure, I'm sure.

122
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:08,800
I'm just a little concerned
about that big baldy.

123
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:18,000
Let me first congratulate our athletes
on a splendid performance...

124
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:21,600
and let me remind them that
only the top four finishers...

125
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:27,400
will earn the right to represent
Jamaica in the forthcoming
summer games in Seoul, Korea.

126
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:30,700
Wait. Y-You're Derice Bannock,
right?

127
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:34,000
- That's me.
- Oh. I hope I make the team.

128
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:39,600
-It would be a real honour to
run with you. Good luck to you.
-Good luck to you.

129
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:43,100
Derice Bannock.
Hey, good luck to you too.

130
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:49,100
Runners, take your marks.

131
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:02,100
Get set!

132
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:50,200
Mr Coolidge, please,
you have to run the race over!

133
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,800
I'm sorry, Derice.
Nothing can be done.

134
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,900
But I was born to compete
in the Olympics!

135
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:57,700
Then you're going to have to work
on your boxing or your cycling.

136
00:09:57,900 --> 00:10:00,500
Those are the only other two sports
in which Jamaica competes.

137
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:03,500
I am not a boxer,
I am a runner.

138
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:06,000
And it wasn't fair.

139
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:09,400
It rarely is, my boy.
It rarely is.

140
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:17,400
Well, Papa, what do I do now?

141
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:21,800
Look, Derice, let it go, eh?
Let it go.

142
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:24,700
You'll have another chance
in four years.

143
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,800
Yeah.

144
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,800
Mr Coolidge...

145
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:34,500
who is the other man in
the picture with my father?

146
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:37,100
Irving Blitzer. He's an
American who lives here.

147
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:40,800
- Unless, of course, he's
been arrested or shot.
- Excuse me?

148
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:43,000
Well, he's a bookie now.

149
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:46,400
Takes his bets in a small
pool hall just past Sandy Bay.

150
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:49,700
- Isn't that a gold medal
around his neck?
- Oh, yeah.

151
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:55,200
That lunatic was an Olympic
bobsledder who tried to get
your father to switch sports.

152
00:10:55,700 --> 00:11:00,000
He had some theory about using
track sprinters to push the bobsleds.

153
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:02,600
Some ridiculous
thing like that.

154
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,400
Can you imagine
a Jamaican bobsledder?

155
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:10,900
And you're sure this man,
he lives on the island?

156
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:13,100
- Oh, yes.
- Mr Coolidge, thanks a lot.

157
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:16,400
- Good, Derice.
- Oh, could I borrow this picture?

158
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:20,600
- Bring it back!
- Yes, sir. Thanks a lot, Mr Coolidge.

159
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:24,200
- Oh, just one more thing.
- Mmm?

160
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:26,700
What's a bobsled?

161
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:30,500
That's a bobsled.

162
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:34,400
Oh. So a bobsled is
a pushcart with no wheels.

163
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:37,600
-That's what it looks like here.
-Let me see that.

164
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:45,300
All right. "The key elements
for a successful sled team...

165
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:49,800
are a steady driver
and three strong runners
to push off down the ice."

166
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:53,200
Ice? lce?

167
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:55,200
Well...

168
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,800
it's kind of a
winter sport, you know.

169
00:11:59,100 --> 00:12:02,900
- You mean winter, as in ice?
- Maybe.

170
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:07,600
You mean winter, as in igloos
and Eskimos and penguins and ice?

171
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:10,400
- Possibly.
- See you.

172
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:12,400
Where you going?

173
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:15,500
I'm going to take a hot bath.
I'm getting cold just thinking
about all this ice.

174
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:20,100
- No, man! You're going to be
part of my bobsled team!
- What do you need me for?

175
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:24,700
Who is the best pushcart driver
in all o' Jamaica?

176
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,800
- You're looking at him?
- Then you're going to do it?

177
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,000
No!

178
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:31,200
Hey, man, you could be famous.

179
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:34,800
You could have your picture
on a Wheaties box.

180
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:38,800
But you said "no," and that's
all right, because I don't need you.

181
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:42,400
Everybody is going to want
to be on my bobsled team!

182
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:45,700
Look, star, let me tell you
a little something, all right?

183
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:49,300
When you need something from me, you
don't have to hand me a bunch of lines.

184
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:52,800
All you have to do is
look at me in the eye and say,
"Sanka, you are my best friend.

185
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:56,200
We been through a whole heap together
and I really, really need you."

186
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:03,000
Sanka, you're right.
And you are my best friend.

187
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:05,900
- And we've been through
a whole lot together.
- Heap. Heap.

188
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:08,900
Sorry, man.
Whole heap together.

189
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:13,400
- "And I really, really need you."
- And I really, really need you.

190
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:15,600
- Forget it.
- But you just said if I said that--

191
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:19,500
All right.
All right, all right. All right, man.

192
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,000
So, let's talk about
this bill-sled team.

193
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,800
- No, bobsled team.
- Whoever.

194
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:29,600
Now, about the Wheaties box--
I'm going to be on it by myself, right?

195
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,100
No, man, you're going to
be on it with me.

196
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:34,600
And down the stretch they come!
Tumbleweed is holding on...

197
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:37,000
- as Captain Video makes it
all the way on the outside.
- Yes, Tumbleweed, yes!

198
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:39,500
- Come on! That's it!
- Brewster is dropping back
as Tumbleweed holds the rail.

199
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,800
- Good Tumbleweed! Good Tumbleweed!
- And here comes Captain Video
on the outside!

200
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:46,300
- Tumbleweed is slowing!
- No, Tumbleweed! No! Bad
Tumbleweed! What are you doing?

201
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:49,000
- Tumbleweed can't hold it and he
gets pinned against the rail.
- What? Don't do--

202
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,100
- It's anyone's race
as they approach the rail!
- Don't do that! Let him out!

203
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,500
- Captain Video makes his move!
Tumbleweed is running gamely...
- No! I need this one!

204
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:56,000
- but Captain Video seems
just a little bit too strong!
- Please! Come on!

205
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:58,100
- Here they come!
- No!

206
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:01,200
Yes! Tumbleweed can't hold it,
as Captain Video takes charge.

207
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:04,600
And it's Brewster finishing in second,
Susan's Pride finishes third...

208
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:06,900
and Tumbleweed
is nowhere in sight!

209
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:09,200
But, my, oh, my,
the odds-on favourite...

210
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:11,900
- showed his true colours
with that late-stretch run.
- That's all right. Uh-huh.

211
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:14,200
Tumbleweed held on momentarily,
but realistically...

212
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:16,500
only a fool would put
their money on Tumbleweed.

213
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:18,500
That horse had no chance of--

214
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:26,000
That guy won two gold medals?

215
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,500
I think so.

216
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:38,600
That's Tumbleweed gone.

217
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,500
Okay, next race.

218
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:47,200
Excuse me. Are you
Mr lrving Blitzer?

219
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,700
Well, that depends
on who's asking.

220
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:53,300
My name is Derice Bannock.
This is my teammate Sanka Coffie.

221
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:55,700
Greetings, sled god.

222
00:14:55,900 --> 00:15:01,300
We were just wondering if you'd
be interested in coaching the
first Jamaican bobsled team.

223
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:05,500
Derice, remember the radio?
Radio?

224
00:15:05,700 --> 00:15:08,500
Stick. Shooting with the stick.
Let's go!

225
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:10,500
Let's go, Derice!

226
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:26,000
Come on, Coach.

227
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:28,000
Just help me get started!

228
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:43,100
- Greetings, sled god.
- Sorry to bother you...

229
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:45,400
- Get out! Get out!
- but you're the only one
that can help us!

230
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:56,700
- Go away.
- Okay.

