in twenty years.

253
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,900
Huh! Would you look at me then.

254
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:30,300
- Ooh. Would you look at me now?
- Please, Mr Blitzer.

255
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,100
Just give me a chance.

256
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,200
If I don't have what it takes,
we forget the whole thing.

257
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:39,300
- Believe me, kid, you do not
have what it takes.
- But you thought my father did.

258
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:44,000
Your father was one of
the toughest competitors I ever saw.

259
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:47,100
He ran the 100 metres
in ten-flat.

260
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,100
Well, I run it in 9.9.

261
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:55,600
Come on. Coach me.

262
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:01,900
Sorry. You're a couple
decades late.

263
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:04,300
Oh, I see. Well, it might be
easy for you...

264
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:06,300
