485
00:33:38,300 --> 00:33:41,200
Uh, Derice, if I hadn't
tripped you fellas...

486
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:45,500
we'd already have been going
to the Olympics; I want you to have it.

487
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:53,900
You mean you want us
to have it, right?

488
00:33:54,100 --> 00:33:56,100
Right. Us.

489
00:33:58,500 --> 00:34:01,000
Thanks a lot, Junior.
Thanks a whole heap, man.

490
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:06,000
Remember, this doesn't mean
that I like you, you understand?

491
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:10,300
Be sure to thank your father for
us, 'cause Lord knows, he didn't
have to let you sell that car.

492
00:34:10,700 --> 00:34:13,300
Well, uh, he doesn't know
I sold the car.

493
00:34:13,500 --> 00:34:17,600
Um, he doesn't know
I'm on the team.

494
00:34:17,900 --> 00:34:20,200
He thinks I'm off to Miami...

495
00:34:20,500 --> 00:34:22,300
and I loaned the car
