503
00:35:23,500 --> 00:35:29,100
Welcome to Calgary, Alberta, Canada,
home of the 1988 Winter Olympic Games.

504
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:32,300
- This is it.
- We hope you all enjoy your stay.

505
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:10,600
Sanka, man, what you smokin'?

506
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:13,300
I'm not smokin'.
I'm breathin'.

507
00:36:16,300 --> 00:36:19,900
- All right, fellas,
this is us. Let's go!
- Move! Let's go! Move!

508
00:36:20,300 --> 00:36:22,400
- Aah! Me first!
- What's the matter? You guys cold?

509
00:36:24,200 --> 00:36:27,200
It's not so much the heat; it's
the humidity that'll kill you.

510
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:16,100
Excuse me, do you know where
you can register for bobsled?

511
00:37:21,700 --> 00:37:24,000
Do you know where you
register for bobsled?

512
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:31,800
- See you.
- I'll see you around.

513
00:37:34,300 --> 00:37:37,200
- Okay, Mike, good to see you again.
- Ja?

514
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:39,400
- Take care. All the best.
- Ja? Okay, ja.

515
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:44,200
- Can I help you?
- Yeah, I'd like to
register for the tryouts.

516
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:47,100
- What country?
- Uh, Jamaica.

517
00:37:47,500 --> 00:37:49,000
What country?

518
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:50,600
Jamaica.

519
00:37:54,100 --> 00:37:58,200
Well, what do you know?
A Jamaican bobsled team.

520
00:37:58,500 --> 00:38:00,300
Okay, here it is.

521
00:38:00,600 --> 00:38:04,400
Uh, it says here your qualifying run
will be held on the evening of the 10th.

522
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:07,500
Your judges will be Shindler,
Gremmer and Kroychzech.

523
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:11,500
- I know Kroychzech. He's a good guy.
- Yeah.

524
00:38:11,800 --> 00:38:16,900
In order to qualify, you must
complete the course safely in 1
minute, 2 seconds-flat or under.

525
00:38:17,300 --> 00:38:20,000
- Used to be a minute, five.
- Yeah.

526
00:38:20,200 --> 00:38:22,200
Times change.

527
00:38:27,600 --> 00:38:30,600
- Irv, is that you?
- Roger, how you doing?

528
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:33,100
Hello, Kurt.
Been a long time.

529
00:38:36,100 --> 00:38:38,300
Obviously not long enough.

530
00:38:38,600 --> 00:38:42,300
- Hello, Larry.
- Jesus Christ, lrv.

531
00:38:42,600 --> 00:38:44,600
What the hell did you
do to yourself?

532
00:38:46,900 --> 00:38:49,300
- Don't worry about them, lrv.
- Roger, you got to do me a favour.

533
00:38:49,500 --> 00:38:51,800
- What?
- Please. You know that
revolving restaurant thing?

534
00:38:52,100 --> 00:38:53,800
- Yeah.
- Meet me there in half an hour.
- Half an hour?

535
00:38:54,100 --> 00:38:56,200
- Yeah. Please!
- Roger, come on!

536
00:38:56,500 --> 00:38:58,200
I'll try.

537
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:18,300
- Thanks, Roger.
- Yeah, well-- What's up, lrv?

538
00:39:18,600 --> 00:39:20,400
- How about a drink?
- No, I'm fine.

539
00:39:20,700 --> 00:39:23,000
- What's so important
that it couldn't wait?
- Want something to eat?

540
00:39:23,200 --> 00:39:25,900
- No, I'm fine!
- A salad or something?
- Irv!

541
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:33,000
- I need a sled.
- You came all the way
to Calgary without a sled?

542
00:39:33,300 --> 00:39:36,500
I got 4,800 dollars.
I just need something competitive.

543
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:39,700
- For five grand?
- I know you got something
lying around, Roger.

544
00:39:40,100 --> 00:39:41,800
- But, lrv--
- Anything.

545
00:39:42,100 --> 00:39:45,400
- You know I can't do that.
- Now, wait a minute, Roger.

546
00:39:45,600 --> 00:39:49,600
Remember when you were desperate
to make that last slot on the
'68 Grenoble team...

547
00:39:49,900 --> 00:39:51,800
and you pleaded with me
to talk to Kurt?

548
00:39:52,100 --> 00:39:54,300
Did I say, "Sorry, Roger,
I can't do it"?

549
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:57,300
Come on, don't make me beg.

550
00:39:57,600 --> 00:40:00,300
Roger, it's me.

551
00:40:00,500 --> 00:40:03,600
All right, maybe I can get you
one of our practise sleds.

552
00:40:03,900 --> 00:40:06,600
You're a saint, you know that?
A saint! You haven't changed
a bit! You're still a saint!

553
00:40:06,900 --> 00:40:09,900
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, look, don't get
all mushy on me. Just tell me one thing.

554
00:40:10,200 --> 00:40:14,700
Is this whole thing a big joke,
or do you really expect these
Jamaicans to qualify?

555
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:18,900
Not only are they going to
qualify, they're going to
turn some heads doing it.

556
00:40:19,300 --> 00:40:24,200
Listen, three of these guys
can run the hundred in under ten-flat.

557
00:40:24,500 --> 00:40:26,800
I don't care who you are,
that's lightning.

558
00:40:27,100 --> 00:40:30,100
Yeah, but can lightning
run on ice?

559
00:40:49,300 --> 00:40:51,000
No problem, man.

560
00:40:55,300 --> 00:40:57,100
God!

561
00:41:05,100 --> 00:41:08,700
Irv, these special shoes
aren't very effective.

562
00:41:19,800 --> 00:41:22,200
Grip with your toes!

563
00:41:22,500 --> 00:41:25,000
All right, you sugar-coated
track stars!

564
00:41:25,200 --> 00:41:28,700
Move out and let the ice rasta
show you how it's done.

565
00:41:30,900 --> 00:41:34,500
- Yeah. Like that, yeah. Good.
- Hey, fellas!

566
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:37,400
- Look at my progress.
- Stop touching me!

567
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:50,400
All right, fellas, that's it!
Let's get off the ice before practise.

568
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:53,600
- What practise?
- That practise.

569
00:42:09,300 --> 00:42:11,100
That's right.

570
00:42:14,900 --> 00:42:16,700
Good team this year.

571
00:42:54,900 --> 00:42:59,400
Ein, zwei, drei!

572
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:19,900
Oh, man, you should see this
on the hill.

573
00:44:20,200 --> 00:44:22,600
- It's like a miracle.
- What's "Schweiz"?

574
00:44:22,800 --> 00:44:26,400
- No, man! Swiss!
- This is the real thing, man.

575
00:44:26,600 --> 00:44:28,700
Gentlemen...

576
00:44:28,900 --> 00:44:31,900
I'd like to introduce you to
the newest member of our team.

577
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:42,200
Um, you won't believe what I
had to go through to get us
a sled in such good shape.

578
00:44:42,700 --> 00:44:44,400
Uh--

579
00:44:45,800 --> 00:44:48,300
If we're going to make it
into the Olympics...

580
00:44:48,500 --> 00:44:51,600
this is the boat that's
going to take us there.

581
00:44:51,900 --> 00:44:54,300
Well, I'm-- I'm told
she's actually quite fast.

582
00:44:57,400 --> 00:45:00,000
I, uh, know she's not
much to look at...

583
00:45:00,200 --> 00:45:03,500
- but, uh--
- Shh! She's beautiful!

584
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:19,900
All coaches must sign teams in
before approaching bob run.

585
00:45:41,400 --> 00:45:43,200
Here we go.

586
00:45:45,600 --> 00:45:47,400
Let's go! Let's go!

587
00:45:49,400 --> 00:45:51,200
- Hold on a minute.
- All right, come on.

588
00:45:53,500 --> 00:45:55,300
Here we go.

